.TH OKUMAN 1 "16 June 2026" "OKU Foundation" "Usage Manual"
.SH NAME
.B okuman
\(en the minimalist Oku manual page viewer
.SH SYNOPSIS

\fBokuman\fP
.RB [ -w ]
.RB [ -M
.IR path ]
.RI [ section ]
.I page ...

.SH DESCRIPTION

The
.B okuman
utility finds and displays online manual pages containing documentation for 
utilities, compilers, and programming interfaces within the OKU ecosystem. 

True to the OKU philosophy,
.B okuman
strives for absolute minimalism. It formats and renders documentation directly 
to standard output using native terminal mechanisms, avoiding external terminal 
pager dependencies or complex macro rendering sub-layers. Documentation is 
treated simply: knowledge intended to be unencumbered, readable, and instantly 
accessible to the user.

If a
.I section
is specified,
.B okuman
looks only in that specific section of the manual. Otherwise, it searches all 
available sections in a predefined order and displays the first match found.

.SH OPTIONS

.IP \fB-M\fP\ \fIpath\fP
Specify an alternate colon-separated search path for manual pages. This 
overrides the default system documentation paths and the
.B OKUMANPATH
environment variable.
.IP \fB-w\fP
Do not display the manual page content. Instead, print the absolute path of 
the file or files that would be formatted and displayed.

.SH INPUT FILES AND SECTIONS

Manual pages are organized into numbered sections, typically matching standard 
conventions:
.IP \fB1\fP
User commands and general utilities (e.g.,
.BR okumake (1),
.BR okucc (1)).
.IP \fB2\fP
System calls and direct kernel interfaces.
.IP \fB3\fP
C library functions and header-only APIs.
.IP \fB5\fP
File formats and configuration specifications.
.IP \fB7\fP
Miscellaneous overviews and protocols.

.SH ENVIRONMENT

.IP \fBOKUMANPATH\fP
If set, its value is a colon-separated list of directories used to search for 
manual pages, parsed before the default fallback paths.

